Preheat a well-oiled #grill{} to medium-high heat. (TIP: If using a #grill pan{}, you'll heat it in Step 2.) Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 3⁄4-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until fork-tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain and rinse under cold water; transfer to a #large bowl{} and let cool completely.

> TIP: Spread potatoes out around edges of the bowl to help them cool more quickly.

While potatoes cook, roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(for 4 servings, zest one lemon and quarter both). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; roughly chop leaves. Quarter @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}.

> TIP: If using a grill pan, add a drizzle of oil and heat over medium-high heat now.

== Herb Butter ==

Place @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}.

Stir in half the parsley and a pinch of lemon zest (big pinch of zest for 4) until combined. Set aside.

== Steak ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Add steak to grill (or grill pan, working in batches for 4 servings if needed); grill to desired doneness, ~{4-8%minutes} per side (grills can vary).

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Potato Salad ==

To bowl with cooled potatoes, add @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @dijon mustard{4%teaspoon}, remaining parsley, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings); stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and refrigerate until ready to serve.

In a second large bowl, whisk together remaining mustard, @olive oil{3%tablespoon}, and juice from two lemon wedges (6 TBSP olive oil and four wedges for 4); season with salt and pepper. Add lettuce and tomatoes to bowl; toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, green salad, and potato salad between plates. Top steak with herb butter and juice from remaining lemon wedges. Sprinkle green salad with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} and serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.